  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Golden Visa application involves several steps, typically taking 4-8 months from start to receiving your residence permit. Processing times have increased significantly since SEF was renamed to AIMA in 2023.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Initial Consultation and Investment Selection</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Work with a qualified immigration lawyer and investment advisor. Decide on your investment route (funds, capital, job creation). Research qualifying investment funds if going that route. Budget €5,000-15,000 for professional fees.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Obtain NIF (Portuguese Tax Number)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">You need a Número de Identificação Fiscal (NIF) before you can invest. Non-residents require a fiscal representative. Your lawyer can arrange this, or you can do it in person at a Portuguese tax office. Cost: free to €200.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Open Portuguese Bank Account</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Required for the investment transfer. Some banks allow remote opening; others require an in-person visit. Recommended banks: Millennium BCP, Novo Banco, ActivoBank. Bring NIF, passport, proof of address, and proof of income source.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Complete Qualifying Investment</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Transfer funds and complete your investment. For investment funds, subscribe through your Portuguese bank or directly with the fund manager. Obtain investment confirmation documents—these are essential for your application.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Obtain Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Arrange qualifying health insurance before submitting your application. Get a policy certificate or confirmation letter in English or Portuguese. Ensure it explicitly states coverage in Portugal with no annual limits.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather Documents</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Compile required documents: passport, criminal record certificate (from home country), investment proof, health insurance, proof of accommodation in Portugal (rental or hotel booking for biometrics trip), and proof of funds for living expenses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Application to AIMA</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Your lawyer submits the application online through the AIMA (formerly SEF) platform. Pay the application fee (€5,324.60 per person). You'll receive a confirmation and case number.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for Approval and Schedule Biometrics</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">AIMA reviews your application (currently 2-6 months due to backlog). Once approved, you'll be invited to attend a biometrics appointment in Portugal. This requires physical presence—you cannot do it remotely.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">9</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Attend Biometrics Appointment</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Travel to Portugal for your appointment at an AIMA office. Bring your passport and all original documents. Fingerprints and photo will be taken. This visit can count toward your 7-day annual requirement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">10</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Residence Permit</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Your residence permit card arrives 2-4 weeks after biometrics, either by mail or pickup. The initial permit is valid for 2 years. Congratulations—you're now a Portuguese resident.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Processing delays:</strong> Since SEF was reorganized into AIMA in late 2023, processing times have significantly increased. Applications that once took 2-3 months are now taking 4-6+ months. Budget extra time and maintain patience with the process.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

